<br>
I know you can tank with a non proccing 2her, I've done it with my Rocksmasher, but it wasn't on purpose. I was lagged so bad I didn't realise the MT had gone down, so I was tanking and not taunting for 50% of the entire fight with aggro, so yes, it deffinitely can be done.<br>
<br>
The point is, when your defensive, your DPS sucks, not just sucks, it BLOWS. So, if you can't entirely count on your DPS, proximity, positioning, etc...why NOT use weapons with good aggro procs? Willsapper is 13/20, not exactly a shabby ratio, and fairly speedy, and it packs a nice aggro proc.<br>
<br>
Basically, I figure if I can save 1 monk, or one rogue from having to turn attack off (or god forbid die) to lose aggro for 10 seconds by using proccing wapons over superior ratio weapons, I've MORE than made up for the DPS I lose by using Willsapper/red epic over some better DPS setup. <p><table width="300" border="0" align="center" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0" bgcolor="#003366">
